==Restoration of Tōdai-ji Seven-tiered Pagoda==
[[File:Furukawa Pavilion.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The central seven‐tiered pagoda is represented by {{ill|Furukawa Pavilion|de|Furukawa Pavillon|ja|古河パビリオン|12=draft}}]] The {{ill|Japan World Exposition|de|Weltausstellung Japan|ja|日本万国博覧会|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Furukawa Pavilion|de|Furukawa Pavillon|ja|古河パビリオン|12=draft}} was a reproduction of the Tōdai-ji seven‐tiered pagoda. After the exposition ended, the pavilion was demolished, and only the pagoda finial was relocated to the east side of the Great Buddha Hall at {{ill|Tōdai-ji|de|Tōdai-ji|ja|東大寺|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Reconstructed Aspiration: The Finial Etched in History – 1970, Osaka; Reproduction of Tōdai-ji’s Seven-tiered Pagoda|date=2019-05-28|accessdate=2019-05-28|newspaper={{ill|Nikkei|de|Nikkei|ja|日本経済新聞|12=draft}}|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO45318150X20C19A5AA1P00/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805033312/https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO45318150X20C19A5AA1P00/|archivedate=2021-08-05|url-status=live}}</ref>

At Tōdai-ji, there is a master plan for restoring the original temple complex, which includes the reconstruction of the east pagoda. However, the feasibility and timing of actual construction will be determined once further archaeological investigations have progressed.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Basic Plan Outlined for Seven-tiered Pagoda Restoration – Restoration work to begin in the east pagoda district at Tōdai-ji in Nara|date=2013-04-26|accessdate=2017-02-11|newspaper={{ill|Sankei Shimbun|de|Sankei Shimbun|ja|産経新聞|12=draft}}|url=https://www.sankei.com/west/news/130426/wst1304260032-n1.html|deadlinkdate=2023-09-23|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422180951/https://www.sankei.com/west/news/130426/wst1304260032-n1.html|archivedate=2021-04-22}}</ref>
