==Restoration of Tōdai-ji Seven-tiered Pagoda==
[[File:Furukawa Pavilion.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The central seven‐tiered pagoda is represented by {{ill|Furukawa Pavilion|de|Furukawa Pavillon|ja|古河パビリオン|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa Pavilion|qq=}}]] The [[:en:Expo '70|Japan World Exposition]]’s {{ill|Furukawa Pavilion|de|Furukawa Pavillon|ja|古河パビリオン|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa Pavilion|qq=}} was a reproduction of the Tōdai-ji seven‐tiered pagoda. After the exposition ended, the pavilion was demolished, and only the pagoda finial was relocated to the east side of the Great Buddha Hall at [[:en:Tōdai-ji|Tōdai-ji]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Reconstructed Aspiration: The Finial Etched in History – 1970, Osaka; Reproduction of Tōdai-ji’s Seven-tiered Pagoda|date=2019-05-28|accessdate=2019-05-28|newspaper=[[:en:The Nikkei|Nikkei]]|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO45318150X20C19A5AA1P00/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805033312/https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO45318150X20C19A5AA1P00/|archivedate=2021-08-05|url-status=live}}</ref>

At Tōdai-ji, there is a master plan for restoring the original temple complex, which includes the reconstruction of the east pagoda. However, the feasibility and timing of actual construction will be determined once further archaeological investigations have progressed.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Basic Plan Outlined for Seven-tiered Pagoda Restoration – Restoration work to begin in the east pagoda district at Tōdai-ji in Nara|date=2013-04-26|accessdate=2017-02-11|newspaper=[[:en:Sankei Shimbun|Sankei Shimbun]]|url=https://www.sankei.com/west/news/130426/wst1304260032-n1.html|deadlinkdate=2023-09-23|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422180951/https://www.sankei.com/west/news/130426/wst1304260032-n1.html|archivedate=2021-04-22}}</ref>
